    <h2>Who Should Use Copy.ai?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Marketing teams</strong> that need to produce high volumes of copy quickly</li>
      <li><strong>Freelance writers</strong> looking to speed up their workflow</li>
      <li><strong>Small business owners</strong> who can't afford a full-time copywriter</li>
      <li><strong>Social media managers</strong> creating daily content across platforms</li>
      <li><strong>Email marketers</strong> writing campaigns, subject lines, and sequences</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who Should Skip It?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>SEO-focused bloggers</strong> — tools like <a href="/tools">Surfer SEO + Jasper</a> are better for search-optimized content</li>
      <li><strong>Long-form writers</strong> — novels, whitepapers, and research papers need more specialized tools</li>
      <li><strong>Teams needing deep integrations</strong> — no native WordPress, HubSpot, or CMS connections</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our Verdict</h2>
    <p>Copy.ai is a solid AI writing tool that delivers on its core promise: <strong>fast, decent-quality marketing copy</strong>. The free plan lets you test everything risk-free, and the Blog Post Wizard is genuinely impressive for quick drafts.</p>
    <p>It's not the best at everything — Jasper has better SEO integration, Writesonic is cheaper — but Copy.ai hits a sweet spot of <strong>price, features, and ease of use</strong> that makes it our top recommendation for most marketers.</p>
    <p><strong>Our score: 8.2/10</strong></p>

